# Branch naming

When starting work on a ticket or issue, create a branch from the default base branch (`main`) using this pattern:

```
<prefix>/<id>-<short-slug>
```

| Issue type | Prefix | Example |
|------------|--------|---------|
| Feature, enhancement, chore | `feature` | `feature/42-full-width-topbar` |
| Bug fix | `bug` | `bug/17-save-entry-missing` |

## Rules

- **`<id>`** — Ticket or issue identifier (e.g. GitHub issue `#7` → `7`, Jira `PROJ-123` → `PROJ-123`).
- **`<short-slug>`** — Lowercase kebab-case summary of the ticket (2–5 words). Use letters, numbers, and hyphens only.
- Create the branch **before** making changes; do not commit on `main` for ticket work.
- One ticket per branch; keep the slug aligned with the issue title.

## Examples

```
feature/7-journal-topbar-header
feature/PROJ-42-entry-drawer-delete
bug/12-paragraph-save-regression
bug/99-auth-callback-redirect
```

## Avoid

- `cursor/...`, `fix/...`, or date-based names unless the team explicitly uses them
- Spaces, underscores, or uppercase in the slug
- Branches with no issue id when work is tied to a tracked ticket
